creator: Emma Lazarus
description: LibriVox volunteers bring you 19 recordings of Off Rough Point by Emma Lazarus. This was the Fortnightly Poetry project for February 1, 2015. Read in English by elliot; Bruce Kachuk; DomBombadil; David Lawrence; Ezwa; fshort; Garth Burton; Greg Giordano; Ian King; J. Alan Brown; Joe Brenneman; RLC; John Sercel; Acevedo; Larry Wilson; Leonard Wilson; MaryAnn; Maria Kasper and William George. Emma Lazarus was an American poet born in New York City. She is best known for "The New Colossus", a sonnet written in 1883; its lines appear on a bronze plaque in the pedestal of the Statue of Liberty placed in 1903. ( Wikipedia) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
